Prepare host for oracle installation

- Fully update

- Update kernel and verify it latest statement

- Set timezone to Asia/Yekaterinburg

- Set FQDN hostname 
- Check for FQDN name in /etc/hosts

- Add groups for database managment

- Add user Oracle

- Set user Oracle password

- Install requiered packages

- Add kernel parameters

- Apply kernel parameters

- Set shell limits for user oracle in file /etc/security/limits.conf

- Check and disable Firewalld

- Check and disable SELinux

- Modify .bash_profile for user Oracle

- Create directory structure 

- Configure ssh server with X forwarding
 
